# FitCore: shared Gym Owner + Super Admin screens

The web app (`apps/fitcore_gym_owner`) serves **Gym Owner** and **Super Admin** from one codebase. Prefer **one screen per feature** that both roles can use; **only** add a separate route or page when **gym owners must not have access** (true super-admin-only capabilities).

## Rules

1. **Default: shared page components**  
   Implement surfaces both roles need under `src/app/(dashboard)/…` and `src/components/…` once. Drive differences with **RBAC / role** (e.g. `role === "super_admin"` from session or shell context), optional props like `canImpersonate`, or feature flags—not a second copy of the whole page.

2. **Super-admin-only = separate route (and guard)**  
   Features gym owners never see (e.g. cross-tenant gym directory, platform billing, system controls) live on **dedicated routes** with **nav + server/middleware checks** so owners cannot open them. That is the **only** case where a wholly different screen tree is appropriate.

3. **Navigation vs content**  
   `DashboardShell` (or equivalent) may show **different nav items** per role, but **overlapping destinations** should render the **same** page module, optionally branching on permissions inside.

4. **New work**  
   When adding UI: ask “can gym owner see this?” If **yes** → shared screen + permission branches. If **no** → super-admin route only, no duplicate “owner version” of the same layout.

## Anti-patterns

- Duplicating a dashboard or list page as `SuperAdminFoo` and `GymOwnerFoo` when the layout differs only by columns, actions, or copy.
- Putting super-admin-only actions on a shared URL without enforcing **deny by default** for `gym_owner`.

## Good pattern

```tsx
// Shared page; hide or swap actions by role / permissions.
export default function RevenuePage() {
  const role = useDashboardRole(); // gym_owner | super_admin (from auth when wired)
  const showCrossTenant = role === "super_admin";
  return (
    <div>
      <RevenueSummary scope={showCrossTenant ? "platform" : "gym"} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Reference (current prototype nav)

- **Gym owner–oriented routes** (examples): `/`, `/members`, `/trainers`, `/reception`, `/revenue`, `/settings`.
- **Super admin–only style routes** (examples): `/gyms`, `/billing`, `/analytics`, `/system` — keep these **non-duplicative** vs owner pages; do not rebuild owner equivalents unless product requires a **different** IA.

When auth replaces the shell toggle, **preserve** the same rule: shared components, split routes only for capabilities gym owners lack.
